```
The `unfold grow` will expand the definition of `grow 6`. Let's see how many times it will unfold.
`grow 6` will be `grow (4 + 2)`.
This will become `f1 f2` where `f1 := grow 4` and `f2 := grow 5`.
`f1 := grow 4` will be `f1' f2'` where `f1' := grow 2` and `f2' := grow 3`.
`f1' := grow 2` will be `f1'' f2''` where `f1'' := grow 0` and `f2'' := grow 1`.
`f1'' := fun x => x`.
`f2'' := fun x => x`.
So `f1'` is `(fun x => x) (fun x => x) = fun x => x`.
Then `f2'` is `(fun x => x) (fun x => x) = fun x => x`.
So `f1 := (fun x => x) (fun x => x) = fun x => x`.
Then `f2 := (fun x => x) (fun x => x) = fun x => x`.
So `f1 f2` is `(fun x => x) (fun x => x) = fun x => x`.
Therefore, `grow 6 = fun x => x = id`.

The `repeat unfold grow` will perform this expansion.
The `all_goals sorry` is not a valid proof. We need to complete the proof.

